### 4. Sleepy Test — `ProcessOrder_AsyncNotification_IsSent` (line 98)

```csharp
processor.ProcessOrderAsync(order);
Thread.Sleep(2000);
Assert.IsTrue(_email.WasNotificationSent(order.Id));
```

`Thread.Sleep(2000)` is a race condition: too short on slow CI, needlessly slow locally. Every test run pays a 2-second wall-clock penalty.

**Fix:** Make the method properly awaitable, or poll with a timeout:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public async Task ProcessOrder_AsyncNotification_IsSent()
{
    var processor = new OrderProcessor(_db, _email, _inventory);
    var order = new Order { Items = { new OrderItem("SKU-1", 1) } };

    await processor.ProcessOrderAsync(order);

    Assert.IsTrue(_email.WasNotificationSent(order.Id));
}
```

